<http://www.spektrix.com/theisabel/event/56401ANGTJBPDPBRQJTCNQMGHRLLHLQJK> a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Cheng² Duo";
  schema:description """
	JUNO-nominated sibling duo Cheng² Duo, cellist Bryan Cheng and pianist Silvie Cheng, return to the Isabel with the expressive artistry and musical connection that have captivated artists worldwide. Since their debut at Carnegie Hall, the duo has toured internationally to critical acclaim. Their program pairs Maurice Ravel’s <span class=\"ItalicText\">Pavane pour une infante défunte</span> and Modest Mussorgsky’s <span class=\"ItalicText\">Pictures at an Exhibition</span> in the duo’s own arrangement with works by Fazil Say and Dinuk Wijeratne. 
""";
