  schema:name "Leticia Moreno and Friends";
  schema:description """
	<span class=\"ItalicText\">In Bach in the Americas</span>, violinist Leticia Moreno, bandoneonist Claudio Constantini, double bassist Uxia Martinez Botana, and pianist Matan Porat trace the enduring legacy of Johann Sebastian Bach across continents and centuries.<span><br/></span>From Bach’s own Sonata and monumental <span class=\"ItalicText\">Chaconne</span> to Heitor Villa-Lobos’ <span class=\"ItalicText\">Bachianas Brasileiras</span> and Astor Piazzolla’s <span class=\"ItalicText\">Four Seasons of Buenos Aires</span>, this genre-crossing program reveals how Baroque brilliance has taken root throughout North and South America, inspiring vibrant musical voices across the Americas.
""";
